<paragraph id="8B8236D8F01BFFA5FF0DFA3FFBB6FA42" blockId="24.[151,1437,1465,2031]" box="[199,1120,1465,1491]" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">Articulamentum white, weakly developed, apophyses broadly rounded, triangular.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236D8F01BFFA5FF0DFA5BFBC6F93A" blockId="24.[151,1437,1465,2031]" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">
Girdle very narrow, densely covered with small, imbricating, conical scales (50 x 
<quantity id="4CC59B3DF01BFFA5FB9CFA5BFB74FA66" box="[1110,1186,1501,1527]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" unit="mm" value="26.0">26 µm</quantity>
), sometimes truncated at the top, always marked with 4–6 sharp ribs, which are twice less than interstices; intersegmental needles very long and smooth (350 x 
<quantity id="4CC59B3DF01BFFA5FE67F9A3FE2DF9AE" box="[429,507,1573,1599]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 µm</quantity>
). Margin armed with two different kinds of elements: 1) few long smooth needles similar to the intersegmental ones (350 x 
<quantity id="4CC59B3DF01BFFA5FDA4F9CFFD6DF9F2" box="[622,699,1609,1635]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 µm</quantity>
), 2) dorsally finely ribbed (6–7 ribs) sharply pointed scales (80 x 18 μm) Ventral side near margin with one row of small (50–60 x 20 μm), oval, distally obtusely pointed scales with four short ribs in upper half; other ventral scales smooth, pointed (46 x 
<quantity id="4CC59B3DF01BFFA5FC7DF917FBD2F93A" box="[951,1028,1681,1708]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 µm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236D8F01BFFA5FF0DF933FE4EF886" blockId="24.[151,1437,1465,2031]" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">
Radula 
<quantity id="4CC59B3DF01BFFA5FED7F933FEA5F95E" box="[285,371,1717,1743]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
long with 25 transverse rows of mature teeth. Central tooth short, rectangular, with sharp base, first lateral tooth short, triangular, without a blade, major lateral tooth with bidentate cusp, inner denticle much smaller than outer one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8236D8F01BFFA5FF0DF8A7FC85F8AA" blockId="24.[151,1437,1465,2031]" box="[199,851,1825,1851]" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">There are 4 gills per side arranged from valve VII to anus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3276553F01BFFA5FF0DF8C3FB3DF87E" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8236D8F01BFFA5FF0DF8C3FB3DF87E" blockId="24.[151,1437,1465,2031]" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF01BFFA5FF0DF8C3FEEDF8CE" bold="true" box="[199,315,1861,1887]" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species can be easily recognized by the protuberances at the posterior margin of the intermediate valves. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D5BF01BFFA5FE9BF8EFFDA7F812" authority="Sirenko, 2020" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2020" box="[337,625,1897,1923]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="longigranum" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF01BFFA5FE9BF8EFFDA7F812" box="[337,625,1897,1923]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">Leptochiton longigranum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27A57B1F01BFFA5FDB3F8EFFD6EF812" box="[633,696,1897,1923]" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D5BF01BFFA5FCF0F8EFFB6DF812" authority="(Ashby, 1929)" baseAuthorityName="Ashby" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[826,1211,1897,1923]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="finlayi">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF01BFFA5FCF0F8EFFBC7F812" box="[826,1041,1897,1923]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">Leptochiton finlayi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC4B29F01BFFA5FBEBF8EFFB65F812" author="Ashby, E." box="[1057,1203,1897,1923]" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" pagination="366 - 369" refId="ref10535" refString="Ashby, E. (1929) New Zealand fossil Polyplacophora (Chitons). Transactions and Proceedings of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 60, 366 - 369, pl. 32." type="journal article" year="1929">Ashby, 1929</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F32A7648F01BFFA5FACEF8EFFA4AF812" box="[1284,1436,1897,1923]" name="New Zealand" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
which also has protuberances at the posterior margin of the lateral areas, but differs from by having granules arranged in quincunx (vs. granules in head valve, central areas of intermediate valves and antemucronal area of tail valve arranged in longitudinal rows in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D5BF01BFFA5FD83F850FD79F87E" baseAuthorityName="Ashby" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[585,687,2005,2031]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="finlayi">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF01BFFA5FD83F850FD79F87E" box="[585,687,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">L. finlayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and four gills per side (vs. nine gills in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D4D5BF01BFFA5FBBFF850FB0DF87E" baseAuthorityName="Ashby" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1141,1243,2005,2031]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="24" pageNumber="491" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="finlayi">
<emphasis id="B949EACAF01BFFA5FBBFF850FB0DF87E" box="[1141,1243,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="491">L. finlayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
